cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SY, cs.CYBER, cs.CR 

This paper deals with the application of machine learning techniques to capture the inherent aggregate flexibility of a population of appliances in demand response programs. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the challenges associated with demand side management of heterogeneous appliances, which falls under the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes a framework to quantify customer privacy, which is related to Cybersecurity (cs.CYBER) and Cryptography (cs.CR) sub-categories.
